{"id":"hattush","term":"Hattush","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Assembled. (1.) A priest who returned with Zerubbabel (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 12:2\">Neh. 12:2</a>). (2.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 8:2\">Ezra 8:2</a>. (3.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 3:10\">Neh. 3:10</a>. (4.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 10:4\">Neh. 10:4</a>. (5.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 3:22\">1 Chr. 3:22</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Nehemiah 12:2","Ezra 8:2","Nehemiah 3:10","Nehemiah 10:4","1 Chronicles 3:22"]}